- 'Exchanges to miners' represents the financial transactions from cryptocurrency exchanges to miners.

sql:
SELECT AVG(stock_to_flow) AS average_stock_to_flow
FROM financial_indicators
WHERE date = (SELECT MAX(date) FROM financial_indicators);

external_knowledge:
- The Market Value to Realized Value (MVRV) ratio is a metric used to assess the health of a cryptocurrency market by comparing its current market value to its realized value, which is the total value of all coins at the time they were last moved;
- The exchange to miner flow total represents the total amount of cryptocurrency flowing from exchanges to miners, which can indicate market sentiment and miner activity;
- The product of these two metrics (Flow_MVRV_Product) provides a measure of the combined influence of market conditions and miner activity on a given day.

- 'mvrv' (Market Value to Realized Value ratio) is a metric used to understand the financial health of cryptocurrency assets; it compares the current market value of a cryptocurrency to its realized value (the cost basis of all coins);
- 'exchange_to_miner_flow_total' represents the total amount of cryptocurrency flowing from exchanges to miners;
